        "content": "# 📚 SRE Runbook Quick Links\n\n## Critical Incident Response\n\n### 🚨 Immediate Actions\n- **[Incident Response Guide](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/INCIDENT_RESPONSE.md)** - Start here for any critical incident\n  - Escalation matrix and contact information\n  - On-call procedures and handoff protocols\n  - Incident lifecycle management\n  - Post-mortem templates\n\n- **[Rollback Procedures](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/ROLLBACK_PROCEDURES.md)** - Rapid recovery procedures\n  - Blue-green deployment rollback\n  - Configuration rollback procedures\n  - Database migration rollback\n  - Feature flag emergency disable\n\n---\n\n## Debug Playbooks by Symptom\n\n### ⏱️ Performance Issues\n- **[Latency Spike Debugging](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_LATENCY_SPIKE.md)**\n  - Check database connection pools\n  - Analyze slow query logs\n  - Review recent deployments\n  - Inspect downstream service health\n\n- **[High CPU Usage](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_CPU_SPIKE.md)**\n  - Profile application CPU usage\n  - Identify runaway threads\n  - Check for infinite loops\n  - Review recent code changes\n\n### 💾 Memory Issues\n- **[Memory Leak Debugging](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_MEMORY_LEAK.md)**\n  - Heap dump analysis procedures\n  - Memory profiling tools\n  - Common leak patterns\n  - JVM/Python memory tuning\n\n- **[OOM Killer Events](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_OOM.md)**\n  - Container memory limit analysis\n  - Memory request/limit tuning\n  - Application memory optimization\n\n### 🔌 Service Connectivity\n- **[Circuit Breaker Debugging](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_CIRCUIT_BREAKER.md)**\n  - Check downstream service health\n  - Review circuit breaker thresholds\n  - Analyze timeout configurations\n  - Test manual circuit reset\n\n- **[Service Mesh Issues](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_SERVICE_MESH.md)**\n  - Envoy proxy debugging\n  - mTLS certificate verification\n  - Network policy troubleshooting\n\n### 🔥 Container/Pod Issues\n- **[Container Restart Loop](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_RESTART_LOOP.md)**\n  - Check liveness/readiness probes\n  - Review container logs\n  - Analyze resource constraints\n  - Verify environment variables\n\n- **[Pod Eviction](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/DEBUG_POD_EVICTION.md)**\n  - Node pressure conditions\n  - Resource quota exceeded\n  - Priority and preemption rules\n\n---\n\n## Additional Resources\n\n### 📊 Related Dashboards\n- [Platform Overview Dashboard](../platform-overview) - High-level system health\n- [Kong API Gateway Dashboard](../kong-dashboard) - API traffic and errors\n- [Memory Telemetry Dashboard](../memory-telemetry) - Detailed memory analysis\n- [Cost Optimization Dashboard](../cost-optimization) - Resource efficiency\n\n### 🔧 External Tools\n- **[Alertmanager Console](http://localhost:9093)** - Manage alert silences and routing\n- **[Prometheus Targets](http://localhost:9090/targets)** - Check scrape target health\n- **[Grafana Alerting](http://localhost:3000/alerting/list)** - Configure dashboard alerts\n\n### 📖 Documentation\n- **[Disaster Recovery Runbook](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/DISASTER_RECOVERY_RUNBOOK.md)** - Complete system recovery procedures\n- **[Multi-Region Failover](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/MULTI_REGION_FAILOVER_RUNBOOK.md)** - Geographic failover protocols\n- **[On-Call Playbook](https://github.com/organization/repo/blob/main/docs/runbooks/ON_CALL_PLAYBOOK.md)** - On-call engineer responsibilities\n\n---\n\n## 🆘 Escalation\n\n**On-Call Contact**: Check PagerDuty or internal wiki for current on-call rotation\n\n**Escalation Path**:\n1. **0-15 min**: On-call SRE investigates\n2. **15-30 min**: Alert team lead and relevant service owners\n3. **30+ min**: Escalate to Platform Architect and Engineering Manager\n4. **Critical incidents**: Immediately notify incident commander\n\n**Emergency Contact**: `emergency@organization.com` | **Slack**: `#incident-response`",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "10.2.2",
      "title": "Runbook Links & Debug Playbooks",
      "type": "text"
    }
